     Add a Batch Process Request. This request will be executed when the
BatchLauncher is run at a later date. A KeySet called BATCHPREQ is used to
obtain a UniqueID for the process request. This is a human readable key set
that must be configured in advance of a call to this method.

@param processDefName The name of the process to add.
@param paramList This tab delimited string represents the parameter format
for a batch process request. The string is in the form:
<code>&lt;name&gt; \t&lt;value&gt; \t&lt;mandatory&gt; \t&lt;data type&gt;
\t&lt;description&gt;</code>.
Multiple parameters can be added by separating the parameters with newline
('\n') character.
@param userName The user name to associate with the request.
@param deprecated No longer used

@throws DatabaseException Standard database exceptions.
@throws AppException Generic Exception Signature.
@throws AppRuntimeException {@link
curam.util.message.INFRASTRUCTURE#RUN_ID_KEY_SET_NOT_FOUND
RUN_ID_KEY_SET_NOT_FOUND} - if the BATCHPREQ Key Set cannot be found.
@throws InformationalException Generic Exception Signature.
@throws IllegalArgumentException if the paramList does not have 5 entries.

