method.doc:
     Add a new table, including the list of codes, descriptions and annotations
belonging to that table to the database. This method will also assign a
code to be the default code for that table. Should a list of codes be
provided, the defaultCode must either be empty or one of the elements in
the list.

@param tableName The table to be added
@param defaultCode The default code for that table
@param codetableItemTabList A tab delimited string consisting of of tuples
of code, description, annotation, sort order and locale code.

@throws AppException {@link INFRASTRUCTURE#ID_SETDEFAULTCODE_ITEMNOTFOUND
ID_SETDEFAULTCODE_ITEMNOTFOUND} - if the default code is not on this table.
@throws AppException {@link INFRASTRUCTURE#ID_CODETABLEADMIN_CODE_EMPTY
ID_CODETABLEADMIN_CODE_EMPTY} - if an item has an empty code field.
@throws AppException
{@link INFRASTRUCTURE#ID_CODETABLEADMIN_DESCRIPTION_EMPTY
ID_CODETABLEADMIN_DESCRIPTION_EMPTY} - if an item has an empty description
field.
@throws AppException {@link INFRASTRUCTURE#ID_ADDCODETABLE_ITEMDUPREC
ID_ADDCODETABLE_ITEMDUPREC} - if a code table item is not unique.
@throws AppException
{@link INFRASTRUCTURE#ID_ADDCODETABLE_DESCRIPTIONDUPREC
ID_ADDCODETABLE_DESCRIPTIONDUPREC} - if a code table description is not
unique.
@throws AppRuntimeException {@link
INFRASTRUCTURE#RUN_ID_CODETABLEADMIN_UNEXPECTED_END_OF_ITEM
RUN_ID_CODETABLEADMIN_UNEXPECTED_END_OF_ITEM} - if the list of CodeTable
items could not be parsed because it ended unexpectedly while parsing an
item.
@throws DatabaseException Standard database exceptions.
@throws InformationalException Generic Exception Signature.

This method takes in the code table name as a parameter and searches for all code table records where the table name fully or partially matches the table name passed in. The table name passed in may be a full or partial code table name. This search is case insensitive. The first series of characters of the table name passed in must match the first series of characters of the code table record that exists. For example, if 'Se' is passed in, then this method will search for all code tables where the table name starts with the characters 'Se', ignoring the case. The results are returned in alphabetical order sorted by code table name.
@param tableName The full or partial table name of the code table record. @return The list of code table details that match the code table name passed in. These details include: tableName, defaultCode and timeEntered.
@throws AppException Generic Exception @throws InformationalException Generic Exception.

Add a new code table data record. The CODETABLEDATA entity contains the table name, locale identifier and the comments field. This entity is used to store comments for the code table header. This method will allow adding comments for multiple locales for a code table header data.
@param dtls The details of the code table data to be added, which includes the table name associated with the code table, locale code and comment. @throws AppException {@link INFRASTRUCTURE#ID_ADDCODETABLEDATA_TABLE_NAME_EMPTY ID_ADDCODETABLEDATA_TABLE_NAME_EMPTY} - if a code table name is empty. @throws AppException {@link INFRASTRUCTURE#ID_ADDCODETABLEDATA_LOCALE_EMPTY ID_ADDCODETABLEDATA_LOCALE_EMPTY} - if the localeIdentifier is empty. @throws AppException {@link INFRASTRUCTURE#ID_ADDCODETABLEDATA_DUPREC ID_ADDCODETABLEDATA_DUPREC} - if a code table header data is not unique.
@throws InformationalException Generic Exception Signature.

