     This method produces a compacted version of an XML document. A compact
representation is one where the spaces and newlines are removed and the
field markers are changed to be a single character.

@param originalXML The long hand form of the XML document.

@return The compacted version of the XML document.

     This method is called by the system when audit information was generated
from an invocation of audit enabled business method.

@param timeStamp The time at which the method was invoked.
@param userId The user who invoked the method.
@param programName The signature of the method which was invoked. This is
in the form <code>BPOName_MethodName</code> (for example
<code>Users_checkSecurity</code>).
@param tranType The context in which the method was invoked. This may be
one of batch, online, deferred and other.

@throws AppException If an exception is thrown the transaction associated
with the business method will be rolled back and no audit information will
be logged.
@throws InformationalException Generic Exception Signature.

     This method is called by the system when audit information was generated
from an invocation of audit enabled database operation.

@param timeStamp The time at which the database operation was invoked.
@param userId The user who invoked the database operation.
@param programName The signature of the database operation which was
invoked. This is in the form <code>BPOName_MethodName</code> (for example
<code>Users_checkSecurity</code>).
@param tranType The context in which the method was invoked. This may be
one of batch, online, deferred and other.
@param tableName The name of the entity being audited.
@param keyRepresentation An XML representation of the key that was used as
part of the update operation. This is in the form

<pre>

 &lt;STRUCT&gt;
   &lt;SNAME&gt;Struct_Name&lt;/SNAME&gt;
   &lt;FIELD&gt;
     &lt;FNAME&gt;Some_field_name&lt;/FNAME&gt;
     &lt;TYPE&gt;java.lang.String&lt;/TYPE&gt;
     &lt;VALUE&gt;Some_field_value&lt;/VALUE&gt;
   &lt;/FIELD&gt;
   &lt;FIELD&gt;
     &lt;FNAME&gt;Some_other_field_name&lt;/FNAME&gt;
     &lt;TYPE&gt;java.lang.String&lt;/TYPE&gt;
     &lt;VALUE&gt;Some_other_field_value&lt;/VALUE&gt;
   &lt;/FIELD&gt;
 &lt;/STRUCT&gt;

</pre>

The <code> type </code> setting is the java type (for example
{@link java.lang.String String} or {@link curam.util.type.DateTime DateTime})
that corresponds to the field,
@param beforeRepresentation An XML representation of the the values of the
various fields before they were updated as part of a data access. This may
be an empty string or a string that follows the same format as the
keyRepresentation.
@param afterRepresentation An XML representation of the values of the
various fields as they will be after they are updated as part of a data
access. This may be an empty string or a string that follows the same
format as the keyRepresentation.
@param operationType The operation type that caused the audit record to be
produced.

@throws AppException If an exception is thrown the transaction associated
with the business method will be rolled back and no audit information will
be logged.
@throws InformationalException Generic Exception Signature.

