@throws AppException
{@link curam.util.exception.AppException AppException}- if problem occurred
when executing the method.
@throws InformationalException
{@link curam.util.exception.InformationalException InformationalException}
Generic Exception Signature.

     The method is called within a transaction after execution of database
update/insert/remove operation.

@param keyStruct key structure used when modifying database.
@param dtlsStruct details structure used as when modifying database.
@param stereotype string containing the Curam data access stereotype.
@param tableName name of the database table which was modified.
@param opName name of the operation performed on database.

@throws AppException
{@link curam.util.exception.AppException AppException}- if problem occurred
when executing the method.
@throws InformationalException
{@link curam.util.exception.InformationalException InformationalException}
Generic Exception Signature.

     Executes a SQL statement which will have a singleton result.
The SQL statement result is returned as an object, the type of which is
specified as an input parameter.

There is no validation of the SQL before execution. The SQL should take
the same form as handcrafted SQL in the model. For example:
<code>
SELECT attribute_two
INTO :result
FROM DynamicSQLTestEnt
WHERE attribute_one =:attribute_one;
</code>

The method requires the type of the return object to be defined. The class
of the argument that will be passed to make up the SQL statement should
also be defined, along with a boolean indicator detailing if auditing
should be performed for the SQL statement, and the handcrafted SQL string.

{@link DynamicDataAccess#executeNsMulti(Class, Object, boolean, String)}
should be used to execute a SQL statement with multiple results.

@param rsltClass The class of object returned by this data access.

@param key The class of the argument that will be passed to make up the
