     Sends an e-mail whose message body is encoded as plain text and includes
an attached file that is encoded with the specified MIME type.


The MIME type must be supported by the javax.mail framework, and it must
be compatible with the attachment Object type. In the case where the
attachment is of type
{@link curam.util.type.Blob curam.util.type.Blob} the MIME type will
default to "application/octet-stream".

@param from The e-mail address of the individual sending the message. This
address follows the standards in JavaMail and as such those in RFC-822.
@param subject The text that will make up the subject line of the address.
@param to The e-mail addresses of the individuals to whom the message
should be addressed. Multiple addresses can be separated by a , or ;
(optionally surrounded by &lt;&gt;). The individual addresses follow the
standards in JavaMail and as such those in RFC-822.
@param cc The e-mail addresses of the individuals to whom the message
should be carbon copied. Multiple addresses can be separated by a , or ;
(optionally surrounded by &lt;&gt;). The individual addresses follow the
standards in JavaMail and as such those in RFC-822.
@param bcc The e-mail addresses of the individuals to whom the message
should be blind carbon copied. Multiple addresses can be separated by a ,
or ; (optionally surrounded by &lt;&gt;). The individual addresses follow
the standards in JavaMail and as such those in RFC-822.
@param message The body of the mail itself, containing the message which
 is to be sent to the associated people.
@param attachmentMimeType The MIME type which is associated with the file
to be attached to the message. The MIME type should be of one which is
supported by the javax.mail framework. In the case where the attachment
is of type {@link curam.util.type.Blob curam.util.type.Blob} the MIME
type will default to "application/octet-stream".
@param attachmentFileName The name which will be presented as the
attachment file name.
@param attachment The data to be attached to the email. This must be a
valid Object type that is supported by the specified MIME type. For
example, a binary data attachment of type
{@link curam.util.type.Blob curam.util.type.Blob} should have a MIME type
of "application/octet-stream".

@throws AppException {@link INFRASTRUCTURE#ID_RECIP_EMAIL_ERROR
ID_RECIP_EMAIL_ERROR} - if some of the specified addresses were not valid.
The problematic addresses are listed in the exception's text.
@throws AppException {@link INFRASTRUCTURE#ID_EMPTY_RECIP_EMAIL_ERROR
ID_EMPTY_RECIP_EMAIL_ERROR} - if the specified to address is empty
@throws AppException {@link INFRASTRUCTURE#ID_EMPTY_SENDER_EMAIL_ERROR
ID_EMPTY_SENDER_EMAIL_ERROR} - if the specified from address is empty
@throws AppException {@link INFRASTRUCTURE#ID_UNKNOWN_EMAIL_ERROR
ID_UNKNOWN_EMAIL_ERROR} - if an unknown error occurred when sending the
