class.doc:
   StructCompare is provided as a means of comparing Curam generated
structures. This class is intended to making comparisons during testing
easier since no .equals() exists for these structures. <BR>
Example of usage:

<pre>
SomeStruct object1;
SomeStruct object2;
StructCompare compareObj1 = new StructCompare(object1);
StructCompare compareObj2 = new StructCompare(object2);
assertEquals(compareObj1, compareObj2);
</pre>
or
<pre>
compareObj1.equals(compareObj2);
</pre>
or
<pre>
compareObj1.equals(object2);
</pre>

The .equals() of StructCompare will work with either another
StructCompare instance or alternative an instance of the actual object
being compared.

@author SC/PS

