     Gets a map of all of the property names and their values from the given
resource. If there is no resource for the given locale, the locale
fall-back mechanism will be used. If there is still no resource found, the
map of properties will not have any values. A new, unmodifiable map is
created each time this method is called, so it is best not to call it if
the {@link #getProperty(String, String, Locale)} method would be more
appropriate. Only the <code>get(Object)</code> method on the returned map
is supported and the key must be a string. Resources will be loaded if
required.

