@return String containing the evidence available for the rule set

@throws AppException {@link RULES#ID_RULESTREE_CLASS_ACCESS
ID_RULESTREE_CLASS_ACCESS} - if rules tree cannot be instantiated
@throws AppException {@link RULES#ID_UNKNOWN_RULESET ID_UNKNOWN_RULESET} -
if rule set could not be found
@throws InformationalException Generic Exception Signature.

     This method should be used to calculate the rate value of a given Objective
for a given date range.

This is intended to be used to calculate the rate value of the Objective
for periods other than the delivery period of the case.
<p>
The objectiveName parameter of this method should include the list RDO
description value(s) in square brackets, if the given objective is located
under a list group. The description values can be found in the second
column of each line of the given tag values when they are tokenized with
the tab value as delimiter. If the given Objective is located under the
nested list groups, it may have multiple description values separated with
commas.  Example of the objective name format is
"Employee Objective [John]" where "Employee Objective" is the name of the
objective and "John" is the description value. Since the name of the
objective is optional, the description value surrounded by square
brackets is also valid, example:[John]. If the Objective is not
located under a list group then an empty open and close brackets should be
passed as objectiveName, example:[]. If an empty open and close brackets
are passed in as the objectiveName for the Objective which is located
under a list group then the first tag value (tag value of the first
iteration of the list group) will be used by the Rules engine
for computing the rate.

@param ruleSetIdentifier is a rule set ID
@param claimReferenceNumber is a case ID
@param personReferenceNumber is a person ID
@param objectiveID is an ID of an Objective that has to be calculated
@param objectiveName is the name of Objective
@param fromDate specifies start date for calculation
@param toDate specifies end date for calculation
@param textOfEvidenceToBeUsed is the text of evidence to be used by the
Rules Engine
@param preinitializedRDOs list of preinitialized RDOs, this list must
contain only entries of type ItemGroup. Null is allowed.

@return the numerical value of the Objective converted to String

@throws AppException {@link RULES#ID_RULESTREE_CLASS_ACCESS
ID_RULESTREE_CLASS_ACCESS} - if rules tree cannot be instantiated
@throws AppException {@link RULES#ID_UNKNOWN_RULESET ID_UNKNOWN_RULESET} -
if rule set could not be found
@throws AppException {@link RULES#ID_UNKNOWN_COMPONENT
ID_UNKNOWN_COMPONENT} - if the component cannot be found
@throws InformationalException Generic Exception Signature.

     This method should be used to calculate the rate value of a given Objective
for a given date range. The objectiveName parameter of this method should
include the list RDO description value(s) in square brackets, if the
given objective is located under a list group. The description values can
be found in the second column of each line of the given tag values when
