method.doc:
     Get a DateTime from an ISO 8601 string in the format yyyymmddThhmmss. The
string must be exactly 15 characters long with a 'T' as the ninth
character. the subfields are parsed as integers and then formatted as a
date using java.util.GregorianCalendar. This means that field wrapping can
occur according to the rules used by GregorianCalendar, for instance a
seconds value of 61 would cause the minute value to wrap.

@param isoString the ISO 8601 format string.

@return a new DateTime object

@throws DateConversionException If the string is null, is not the correct
length or does not match the expected format.

