class.doc:
This class is used by methods wishing to limit the size of the task search results. This class extends {@link curam.util.dataaccess.StandardReadmultiOperation}. This is required in order to throw a {@link curam.util.exception.ReadmultiMaxException} when the maximum is exceeded; the standard operation does not do this.
@param <T> The type of each row in the search result set
@author PJ

method.doc:
     Reads a WDO snapshot data overflow from the database. This will be
necessary in the event of the WDO snapshot being larger than would fit in a
single VARCHAR column in the database, in which case the excess data would
have been written to as many VARCHAR records as necessary in the task WDO
snapshot 'overflow' table on the database.

@param taskDtls the details of the task with which the WDO snapshot data to
be read is associated with.

