     Add the contents of a struct to the XML Document. If the struct is null the
contents will not be placed in the document.

@param value The struct to be added.

     Directly add an XML fragment to the document. It is the responsibility of
the client to ensure this fragment matches the relevant parts of the
document type definition described in the XML Guide.

@param xmlFragment A string containing the XML fragment that could have
been built up through the normal document APIs. An example of a fragment is

<pre>

 &lt;STRUCT&gt;
   &lt;SNAME&gt;DWPNotificEvidDtls&lt;/SNAME&gt;
   &lt;FIELD&gt;
     &lt;FNAME&gt;bankAccountAmt&lt;/FNAME&gt;
     &lt;TYPE&gt;SVR_MONEY&lt;/TYPE&gt;
     &lt;VALUE&gt;0.00&lt;/VALUE&gt;
   &lt;/FIELD&gt;
   &lt;FIELD&gt;
     &lt;FNAME&amp;gtbuildingSocietyAmt&amp;lt;/FNAME&gt;
     &lt;TYPE&gt;SVR_MONEY&lt;/TYPE&gt;
     &lt;VALUE&gt;0.00&lt;/VALUE&gt;
   &lt;/FIELD&gt;
 &lt;/STRUCT&gt;

</pre>

@throws AppRuntimeException {@link INFRASTRUCTURE#RUN_ID_RUNTIME
RUN_ID_RUNTIME}- Generic signature that nests any
{@link IOException IOException}.

@see #add(Object)

