method.doc:
     Set the protocol encoding. If the encoding is not supported by the JVM,
then an error will be thrown to this effect.

@see #getEncoding

@param encoding The protocol encoding.

Gets the encoding that will be used for printing within the XMLServer.
This encoding may be set using the XMLPrintStream.setEncoding() method. If the encoding has not been set, then the value of the curam.xmlserver.fileencoding property will be used. If this property has not been set, then the default encoding of UTF-8 will be returned.
@see #setEncoding
@return encoding The encoding.

